UID:DoaUrjuETyN1LgO7OY6b5
SUMMARY:Homework Help
DTSTAMP:20260330T060608Z
DTSTART:20260330T223000Z
DESCRIPTION:Monday\, March 30\, 2026\, 3:30 - 5:30pm\n\nHomework Help volun
	teers will be at this branch to assist K-12 students with school assignmen
	ts during the school year.\n\nLocation Link:\n\nNorthgate Branch\n\nRoom L
	ocation: Meeting Room\n\nRegistration Required: Registration is not requir
	ed.\n\nDetailed Description: If you are working on a tough homework assign
	ment or have questions about a lesson\, come to the Library for Homework H
	elp. We have volunteers who can help with math\, English\, social studies 
	and science.\, Students without homework can read and play learning enrich
	ment games with trained tutors.\, Snacks are provided at every Homework He
	lp: Thanks to the donors of\n\nThe Seattle Public Library Foundation\n\nfo
	r sponsoring this event.\n\nEvent Logistics:\n\n\, Registration is not req
	uired but these programs are very popular and the room capacity can fill u
	p quickly.\, While Homework Help is available to students from kindergarte
	n through 12th grade\, volunteers are not responsible for children\, who s
	hould not be left unsupervised.\,\n\nFind out more about Homework Help.\n\
	nContact Us: If you have questions about this event\,\n\nAsk Us\n\nor call
	 206-386-4636.\n\nADA Accommodations: We can provide accommodations for pe
	ople with disabilities at Library events. Please\n\ncontactLEAP\n\nat leas
	t seven days before the event to request accommodations.\, All Library pro
	grams are free and open to the public.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/eve
	nts/#/details/homework-help/17650270/2026-03-30T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Comm
	unity & Civic
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/homework-help/17650270/20
	26-03-30T00
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-community
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Community & Civic
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:8Rv3lLPNDVtwxQ_7szSWV
SUMMARY:Learn at LANGSTON: Healing Drum Workshop
DTSTAMP:20260330T060608Z
DTSTART:20260331T004500Z
DESCRIPTION:Event Types: Community\,Ethnic/Cultural\,Music\,Training-Cla ss
	es/Workshops\n\nNeighborhoods: Central Area/Squire Park\n\nSponsoring Orga
	nization: LANGSTON\n\nContact: Jahi McGhee\n\nContact Phone: 2066844758\n\
	nContact Email: langston.institute@seattle.gov\n\nAudience: All\n\nPre-Reg
	ister: Yes\n\nCost: Free\n\nLink: https://www.langstonseattle.org/programs
	/healing-drum-workshop/\n\nDrums are provided. All ages. No experience nec
	essary.\n\nThe Hawk Foundation for Research and Education in African Cultu
	re brings master drummers t o LANGSTON to engage in a well-researched peda
	gogy of community healing through African drumming.\n\nThe Hawk Foundation
	 is a Washington-based drum and education organization that utilizes West 
	African and African American music to promote education\, team bonding\, o
	rganizational de velopment\, and research-based therapy. Through history\,
	 Yoruba stories and classic drum rhythms\, this class has reconnected stud
	ents to the drum\, the past\, and themselves.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.
	com/events/#/details/learn-at-langston-healing-drum-workshop/18448016/2026
	-03-30T00\n\nFrom SEAtoday - Community & Civic
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/learn-at-langston-healing
	-drum-workshop/18448016/2026-03-30T00
LOCATION:Langston Hughes Performing Arts Institute\, 104 17th Avenue South 
	West Room\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-community
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Community & Civic
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT45M
END:VEVENT
