BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:1OTlVf2EWeFW6TDZg8L8-
SUMMARY:Forest Restoration at Greg Davis Park
DTSTAMP:20260330T060608Z
DTSTART:20260331T100000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us for a restoration work party at West Seattle Golf Cours
	e. \\nJoin the DNDA Nature program and help restore important habitat in t
	he critical Longfellow Creek Watershed. Each work party begins with a shor
	t informal forest ecology discussion and we spend the remainder of the tim
	e performing various restoration activities\\\, including planting native 
	trees and shrubs\\\, removing invasive species\\\, mulching previously-pla
	nted areas and more. We work rain or shine! \\nRegister\n\nhttps://www.sea
	ttleparksfoundation.org/event/forest-restoration-at-greg-davis-park/\n\nFr
	om The Seattle Parks Foundation
URL:https://www.seattleparksfoundation.org/event/forest-restoration-at-greg
	-davis-park/
LOCATION:WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seattle-parks-foundation
CATEGORIES:The Seattle Parks Foundation
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:QM1-z4eo_qSV3AlJOONTS
SUMMARY:Moomins' Sea Adventures & Tove and the Sea
DTSTAMP:20260330T060608Z
DTSTART:20260331T170000Z
DESCRIPTION:Dive into the whimsical world of Moominvalley and the life of i
	ts creator\, Tove Jansson\, with *Moomins’ Sea Adventures* and *Tove and t
	he Sea*.\n\n*Moomins’ Sea Adventures* brings Moominvalley to life with ill
	ustrations and life-sized characters from the stories. In the center of th
	e exhibit is an interactive island complete with a lighthouse and rowboats
	 that invites visitors to imagine adventures of their own.\n\n*Tove and th
	e Sea* offers a more intimate counterpoint\, tracing Tove Jansson’s lifelo
	ng relationship with the Finnish archipelago through large-scale photograp
	hs and reflective texts.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/
	moomins-sea-adventures-tove-and-the-sea/18406909/2026-03-31T00\n\nFrom SEA
	today - Community & Civic
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/moomins-sea-adventures-to
	ve-and-the-sea/18406909/2026-03-31T00
LOCATION:National Nordic Museum\, 2655 NW Market Street\, Seattle\, WA
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:seatoday-community
CATEGORIES:SEAtoday - Community & Civic
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT7H
END:VEVENT
